{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/blog/2024-06-28-how-to-add-height-and-width-to-image-in-react-js/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"excerpt":"Hi Friends üëã, Welcome To aHoisting! To add height and width to image in react js, you can set  and  in . It will add height and width to image in react js‚Ä¶","html":"<p>Hi Friends üëã,</p>\n<p>Welcome To aHoisting!</p>\n<p>To add height and width to image in react js, you can set <code class=\"language-text\">width: 200px;</code> and <code class=\"language-text\"> height: 100px;</code> in <code class=\"language-text\">.image-class</code>. It will add height and width to image in react js.</p>\n<p>Today, I am going to show you, how to add height and width to image in react js.</p>\n<p>Table of contents</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Install and create a new React app.</li>\n<li>Import react component.</li>\n<li>Create a Component.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Let‚Äôs start with the first step.</p>\n<h2>Step 1: Install and create a new React app.</h2>\n<p>First you have to install the React project. You should use <code class=\"language-text\">create-react-app</code> command to create a new React project.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">npx create<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>react<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app my<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app\ncd my<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app\nnpm start</code></pre></div>\n<h2>Step 2: Import react component.</h2>\n<p>After installing, you have to import your React component. To do this, add the following line to the top of your component file.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token string\">'./App.css'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<h2>Step 3: Create a Component.</h2>\n<p>You can use <code class=\"language-text\">src=\"collection-dry-autumn-leaves.jpg\"</code> to add height and width to image in react js.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>img \n  src<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"collection-dry-autumn-leaves.jpg\"</span> \n  alt<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Sample\"</span>\n  className<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"image-class\"</span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">/</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span></code></pre></div>\n<h2>Define the add height and width to image example.</h2>\n<p>The below code is an example of a React. You have to import <code class=\"language-text\">'./App.css'</code> and set <code class=\"language-text\">width: 200px;</code> and <code class=\"language-text\"> height: 100px;</code> in <code class=\"language-text\">.image-class</code> to add height and width to image in react js.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">App.js</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token string\">'./App.css'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token function-variable function\">App</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>img \n      src<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"collection-dry-autumn-leaves.jpg\"</span> \n      alt<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Sample\"</span>\n      className<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"image-class\"</span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">/</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> App<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">App.css</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"css\"><pre class=\"language-css\"><code class=\"language-css\"><span class=\"token selector\">.image-class</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">width</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> 200px<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> \n  <span class=\"token property\">height</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> 100px<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> \n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>In the above code example, I have used the <code class=\"language-text\">width: 200px;</code> and <code class=\"language-text\"> height: 100px;</code> and add height and width to image in react js.</p>\n<p>Check the output of the above code.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 290px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/4f36a50c8bd9e1cc0b25038f74822a43/60360/height-and-width-to-image.webp\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 79.11392405063292%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/webp;base64,UklGRpYAAABXRUJQVlA4IIoAAAAwBACdASoUABAAPtFUo0uoJKMhsAgBABoJbACdAYw63tbm5pf7H7TP1YAA/nk2uF7Biz/zvtFHC7rb0bUrd0+0Q0I1yNpxaXwdNFN/Xr9TDkaMyqNd19DJTbXVcg/kHGdLXT+hQGXPcLDCFLA4cvroWbOR8Mc/JS/8xi2NoI8d4MtM+N1s0v49yAA='); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"React, add, height, and, width, to, image\"\n        title=\"React, add, height, and, width, to, image\"\n        src=\"/static/4f36a50c8bd9e1cc0b25038f74822a43/60360/height-and-width-to-image.webp\"\n        srcset=\"/static/4f36a50c8bd9e1cc0b25038f74822a43/81b7c/height-and-width-to-image.webp 158w,\n/static/4f36a50c8bd9e1cc0b25038f74822a43/60360/height-and-width-to-image.webp 290w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 290px) 100vw, 290px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>All the best üëç</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"How to add height and width to image in react js?","tags":["React"],"date":"June 28, 2024","description":"Example of add height and width to image in react js with step by step tutorial - aHoisting","social_image":{"absolutePath":"/Users/mac/Documents/hoisting/ahoisting/static/media/template/reactjs.jpg"}}},"prev":{"frontmatter":{"title":"How to add hidden field in react js?"},"fields":{"slug":"/blog/2024-06-29-how-to-add-hidden-field-in-react-js/"}},"next":{"frontmatter":{"title":"How to add hashtag in react js?"},"fields":{"slug":"/blog/2024-06-27-how-to-add-hashtag-in-react-js/"